[{"id":"VR002425","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a string, which is drawn moving horizontally and to the right. The right end of the string is attached to a metal ring, which is placed half way up a vertical rod.\" height=\"285\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR002425.g01.png\" width=\"400\" /></div>\n\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"tgroup cols:2\">\n\t<thead class=\"thead\">\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<th class=\"entry colname:col1\">Amplitude on String <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"centimeters\"><math alttext=\"centimeters\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mo>(</mo><mtext>cm</mtext><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></th>\n\t\t\t<th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Amplitude of Ring <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"centimeters\"><math alttext=\"centimeters\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mo>(</mo><mtext>cm</mtext><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></th>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</thead>\n\t<tbody class=\"tbody\">\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">2.0</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\">0</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">3.0</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\">2.5</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">4.0</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\">3.8</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">5.0</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\">5.0</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\">6.0</td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\">4.5</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A student holds one end of a string. The other end of the string is attached to a metal ring, as shown, that can slide freely on a vertical rod. The student creates a transverse wave that travels along the string. The student changes the amplitude of the wave and measures the amplitude of the motion of the ring. The data are shown in the table. Based on this data, what can be concluded about the polarization of the wave on the string?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR002425_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The wave was vertically polarized.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The wave was horizontally polarized.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The wave was polarized at some angle between vertical and horizontal that was the same for all trials.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The polarization of the wave had various orientations.</p>"],"answer":3}]